title: Grateful Dead Live at Frost Amphitheatre on 1989-05-07
description: Iko Iko, Little Red Rooster, Bertha, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Built To Last, Picasso Moon, Bird Song Foolish Heart, Victim Or The Crime, Crazy Fingers, Women Are Smarter-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Jam-> The Other One-> Black Peter-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: Knockin' On Heaven's Door

reviews.review_text: Sound Great Show, Great Sound with this source.

Awesome crisp sound this board is leagues better than the other source. And the other source has some kind of speaker imbalance. Go with this one for streaming for sure.

For you Phil fans out there, this one is for you.

Frost amphitheatre on 1989 05 07 very long show ,the kind you would want to be at .the chipmunk voice on track 20 is a trip it completly caught me off gaurd ! but those kind of rare oddities is what makes for a keeper ,not just the same old same old .
he's gone is powerful and jerry is feeling it .
I definatly liked this show ,victem or the crime is very solid and the vocals are crisp and clear
exelent sound quality but alittle on the high end whith not quite as much from phil as usual but all the same a great line up for the set list.

not that good I'm not an expert on all aspects of the show's, but I listen to one concert a night. I have to disagree with the other reviews. Picasso Moon was horrible. The quality of the recording didn't sound that great. No great moments and nothing special.
Sony and Cher? Is that "I got you babe" at the beginning of Crazy Fingers? Awesome sound on this source. Hellacious Space>Other One.

this does sound great, but it's one of those annoying boards where the right and left sides are reversed.  i.e. keyboards coming out of the left side and bass and weir coming out of the right side.  you wouldn't think it's a big deal, but it makes recordings intolerable for me.

Supas review is.... Half right. A lot of it is between good and better, and very good SBD. The Picasso Moon is not good. Let's fight over it. If I had my way, they'd have played wave to the wind, which is worse yet better. Its a good show, they sound great, when not doing songs that they barely like, but that's what it is. Still sounds wonderful and is what they sounded like. all good not bad long show. I'm game, let's go......but how do we get there from here? Trump? Jerry knew all about it.
